# Keep the Docker build context small and free of host-only / internal files.
# The Dockerfile copies only pyproject.toml, README.md, src/, and data/; without
# this file the daemon still uploads everything below as build context — most of
# all the multi-GB local virtualenv — slowing every `docker compose up --build`.
# It is also defence-in-depth for Hard Rules 3 & 7: internal docs and any secret
# can never enter an image layer if they never enter the context.

# Local virtualenv (multi-GB) and Python caches
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# VCS + runtime artifacts (models/indexes are built inside the container)
.git/
.gitignore
artifacts/
checkpoints/
mlruns/
ray_results/
*.log

# Secrets / env (never in an image)
.env
.env.local
*.key
*.pem

# Internal / workspace-only (Hard Rule 3) — never ship in an image either
CLAUDE.md
.claude/
docs/
promo/
tests/
build/
dist/
